article.description: Dwight Ramos scored 14 points off the bench and led four players in double-figure scoring as Cal State Fullerton pulled away from Southern Utah late to post a 75-62 win Saturday night.
article.headline: Ramos sparks Cal St-Fullerton past Southern Utah, 75-62
article.linkText: Ramos sparks Cal St-Fullerton past Southern Utah, 75-62
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Dwight Ramos scored 14 points off the bench and led four players in double-figure scoring as Cal State Fullerton pulled away from Southern Utah late to post a 75-62 win Saturday night. Tre Coggins drilled a 3-pointer with 15 minutes left in the game to lift the Titans into the lead for good, 42-39, but the team could not pull away until the closing minutes. Lionheart Leslie and Jackson Rowe each converted two free throws in the final minute to push the Cal State-Fullerton (4-6) lead into double digits. Coggins and Kyle Allman scored 13 and 12 points, respectively, for the Titans and Austen Awosike added another 10 points. CS Fullerton was 24 of 51 from the field (47.1 percent), including 6 of 13 from distance. Randy Onwuasor had 31 points to lead Southern Utah (2-8), but the Thunderbirds remain winless through five road games.
